## 7. Definition of Done for This Module

If you want to know whether the Federal Workforce Literacy Bridge was properly integrated into a Slow AI Kitchen deployment, use this test. The workshop opening referenced the DOL AI Literacy Framework and positioned Slow AI Kitchen as the delivery vehicle. Each of the four instructional modules made at least one explicit connection between a Kitchen step and a DOL content area or delivery principle. The workshop exercise produced a DOL alignment summary as its twelfth output artifact. For workforce development deployments, a pre-workshop readiness assessment addressed digital literacy prerequisites. The facilitator did not treat the DOL mapping as a checklist exercise separate from the method, but as an integrated explanation of why the method works.

If those conditions are met, the organization can document that its AI governance training program is aligned with the U.S. Department of Labor's AI Literacy Framework as released in TEN 07-25 (February 13, 2026).

